cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is about image restoration using a novel framework based on elements from the half quadratic splitting method and proximal operators. The paper focuses on the development of a convolutional network that models the proximal operator as an implicit prior on the image space during training. This approach is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques to solve image restoration problems. Additionally, the paper involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) as it discusses the use of half quadratic splitting method and proximal operators. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it discusses the use of a deep learning framework for image restoration. Finally, the paper involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it discusses the use of image restoration techniques.
